---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import SocialLinks from "../components/SocialLinks.astro";
---

<Layout title="Max Georgopoulos">
  <div class="col-span-full grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-6 px-4 sm:px-6  mx-auto">
    <Header />
    <img
      src="/me.jpeg"
      alt="my face"
      class="col-span-full md:col-start-1 md:col-end-2 mx-auto aspect-square w-full "
    />
    <SocialLinks classes="col-span-full md:col-span-1 md:col-start-1 md:col-end-2 order-last" />
    <p class="-my-1 col-span-full md:col-start-2 md:col-end-4 mx-auto max-w-prose lg:mx-0 xl:basis-3/4">
      Yo! I'm a designer and developer based out of Toronto, but I bum
      around different places. I believe that the boundary between design
      and engineering is artificial — you get the best results by blending
      the two. Lately, I've been inspired by Ryan Singer's design
      techniques, TailwindCSS, and The 2023 Spring Summer Collection from
      Homme Plissé.
    </p>
    
</Layout>
